ernating subarray sum** of a subarray that ranges from index `i` to `j` (**inclusive**, `0 <= i <= j < nums.length`) is `nums[i] - nums[i+1] + nums[i+2] - ... +/- nums[j]`.\n\nGiven a **0-indexed** integer array `nums`, return *the **maximum alternating subarray sum** of any subarray of *`nums`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [3,-1,1,2]\nOutput: 5\nExplanation:\nThe subarray [3,-1,1] has the largest alternating subarray sum.\nThe alternating subarray sum is 3 - (-1) + 1 = 5.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [2,2,2,2,2]\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nThe subarrays [2], [2,2,2], and [2,2,2,2,2] have the largest alternating subarray sum.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2] is 2.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2,2,2] is 2 - 2 + 2 = 2.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2,2,2,2,2] is 2 - 2 + 2 - 2 + 2 = 2.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: nums = [1]\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nThere is only one non-empty subarray, which is [1].\nThe alternating subarray sum is 1.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `-10⁵ <= nums[i] <= 10⁵`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Dynamic Programming"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"A **subarray** of a **0-indexed** integer array is a contiguous **non-empty** sequence of elements within an array.\n\nThe **alternating subarray sum** of a subarray that ranges from index `i` to `j` (**inclusive**, `0 <= i <= j < nums.length`) is `nums[i] - nums[i+1] + nums[i+2] - ... +/- nums[j]`.\n\nGiven a **0-indexed** integer array `nums`, return *the **maximum alternating subarray sum** of any subarray of *`nums`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [3,-1,1,2]\nOutput: 5\nExplanation:\nThe subarray [3,-1,1] has the largest alternating subarray sum.\nThe alternating subarray sum is 3 - (-1) + 1 = 5.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [2,2,2,2,2]\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nThe subarrays [2], [2,2,2], and [2,2,2,2,2] have the largest alternating subarray sum.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2] is 2.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2,2,2] is 2 - 2 + 2 = 2.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2,2,2,2,2] is 2 - 2 + 2 - 2 + 2 = 2.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: nums = [1]\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nThere is only one non-empty subarray, which is [1].\nThe alternating subarray sum is 1.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `-10⁵ <= nums[i] <= 10⁵`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-alternating-subarray-sum/","problemName":"Maximum Alternating Subarray Sum","problemNumber":2036,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"A **subarray** of a **0-indexed** integer array is a contiguous **non-empty** sequence of elements within an array.\n\nThe **alternating subarray sum** of a subarray that ranges from index `i` to `j` (**inclusive**, `0 <= i <= j < nums.length`) is `nums[i] - nums[i+1] + nums[i+2] - ... +/- nums[j]`.\n\nGiven a **0-indexed** integer array `nums`, return *the **maximum alternating subarray sum** of any subarray of *`nums`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [3,-1,1,2]\nOutput: 5\nExplanation:\nThe subarray [3,-1,1] has the largest alternating subarray sum.\nThe alternating subarray sum is 3 - (-1) + 1 = 5.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [2,2,2,2,2]\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nThe subarrays [2], [2,2,2], and [2,2,2,2,2] have the largest alternating subarray sum.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2] is 2.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2,2,2] is 2 - 2 + 2 = 2.\nThe alternating subarray sum of [2,2,2,2,2] is 2 - 2 + 2 