ed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex2drawio.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/2065-ex2drawio.png","sha256":"2af670f76299700d3d814159e15b5d9de2601382f209b478d3783adaa4f4ed47"},{"assetIndex":2,"bytes":21713,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex31drawio.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/2065-ex31drawio.png","sha256":"e7fbfc1980cba13782f1abf7a39d8e861ba423373529a2a3f8f8cbdd6a1c8196"}],"categories":["Array","Backtracking","Graph Theory"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"There is an **undirected** graph with `n` nodes numbered from `0` to `n - 1` (**inclusive**). You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `values` where `values[i]` is the **value **of the `i^(th)` node. You are also given a **0-indexed** 2D integer array `edges`, where each `edges[j] = [uj, vj, timej]` indicates that there is an undirected edge between the nodes `uj` and `vj`, and it takes `timej` seconds to travel between the two nodes. Finally, you are given an integer `maxTime`.\n\nA **valid** **path** in the graph is any path that starts at node `0`, ends at node `0`, and takes **at most** `maxTime` seconds to complete. You may visit the same node multiple times. The **quality** of a valid path is the **sum** of the values of the **unique nodes** visited in the path (each node's value is added **at most once** to the sum).\n\nReturn *the **maximum** quality of a valid path*.\n\n**Note:** There are **at most four** edges connected to each node.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex1drawio.png","sequence":1,"sha256":"8934da163643f341f3bed591a63762662d7f8eb63d486f36ed24096a56689990","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: values = [0,32,10,43], edges = [[0,1,10],[1,2,15],[0,3,10]], maxTime = 49\nOutput: 75\nExplanation:\nOne possible path is 0 -> 1 -> 0 -> 3 -> 0. The total time taken is 10 + 10 + 10 + 10 = 40 <= 49.\nThe nodes visited are 0, 1, and 3, giving a maximal path quality of 0 + 32 + 43 = 75.","type":"code"},{"sequence":3,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex2drawio.png","sequence":4,"sha256":"2af670f76299700d3d814159e15b5d9de2601382f209b478d3783adaa4f4ed47","type":"image"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: values = [5,10,15,20], edges = [[0,1,10],[1,2,10],[0,3,10]], maxTime = 30\nOutput: 25\nExplanation:\nOne possible path is 0 -> 3 -> 0. The total time taken is 10 + 10 = 20 <= 30.\nThe nodes visited are 0 and 3, giving a maximal path quality of 5 + 20 = 25.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex31drawio.png","sequence":7,"sha256":"e7fbfc1980cba13782f1abf7a39d8e861ba423373529a2a3f8f8cbdd6a1c8196","type":"image"},{"sequence":8,"text":"Input: values = [1,2,3,4], edges = [[0,1,10],[1,2,11],[2,3,12],[1,3,13]], maxTime = 50\nOutput: 7\nExplanation:\nOne possible path is 0 -> 1 -> 3 -> 1 -> 0. The total time taken is 10 + 13 + 13 + 10 = 46 <= 50.\nThe nodes visited are 0, 1, and 3, giving a maximal path quality of 1 + 2 + 4 = 7.","type":"code"},{"sequence":9,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `n == values.length`\n\n- `1 <= n <= 1000`\n\n- `0 <= values[i] <= 10⁸`\n\n- `0 <= edges.length <= 2000`\n\n- `edges[j].length == 3 `\n\n- `0 <= uj < vj <= n - 1`\n\n- `10 <= timej, maxTime <= 100`\n\n- All the pairs `[uj, vj]` are **unique**.\n\n- There are **at most four** edges connected to each node.\n\n- The graph may not be connected.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Backtracking","Graph Theory"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Hard","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"There is an **undirected** graph with `n` nodes numbered from `0` to `n - 1` (**inclusive**). You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `values` where `values[i]` is the **value **of the `i^(th)` node. You are also given a **0-indexed** 2D integer array `edges`, where each `edges[j] = [uj, vj, timej]` indicates that there is an undirected edge between the nodes `uj` and `vj`, and it takes `timej` seconds to travel between the two nodes. Finally, you are given an integer `maxTime`.\n\nA **valid** **path** in the graph is any path that starts at node `0`, ends at node `0`, and takes **at most** `maxTime` seconds to complete. You may visit the same node multiple times. The **quality** of a valid path is the **sum** of the values of the **unique nodes** visited in the path (each node's value is added **at most once** to the sum).\n\nReturn *the **maximum** quality of a valid path*.\n\n**Note:** There are **at most four** edges connected to each node.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex1drawio.png]]\n\nInput: values = [0,32,10,43], edges = [[0,1,10],[1,2,15],[0,3,10]], maxTime = 49\nOutput: 75\nExplanation:\nOne possible path is 0 -> 1 -> 0 -> 3 -> 0. The total time taken is 10 + 10 + 10 + 10 = 40 <= 49.\nThe nodes visited are 0, 1, and 3, giving a maximal path quality of 0 + 32 + 43 = 75.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex2drawio.png]]\n\nInput: values = [5,10,15,20], edges = [[0,1,10],[1,2,10],[0,3,10]], maxTime = 30\nOutput: 25\nExplanation:\nOne possible path is 0 -> 3 -> 0. The total time taken is 10 + 10 = 20 <= 30.\nThe nodes visited are 0 and 3, giving a maximal path quality of 5 + 20 = 25.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2065-maximum-path-quality-of-a-graph/2065-ex31drawio.png]]\n\nInput: values = [1,2,3,4], edges = [[0,1,10],[1,2,11],[2,3,12],[1,3,13]], maxTime = 50\nOutput: 7\nExplanation: